Manufacturer: Lenovo
Model Name: Lenovo ThinkPad X201T
Model Number: 

Notes: Uses a sensor connected over the serial bus. Two different types
of hardware have been seen: one reporting itself with PID 0x90 ("data")
and a second reporting a PID of 0xE3 ("sysinfo.PbdMPT7yUD"). In the case
of the former, it has been reported that the touchscreen is provided
by non-Wacom hardware.

Source(s):
 * data
   Tyson Tan [https://sourceforge.net/u/tysontan/profile/]
   https://sourceforge.net/p/linuxwacom/bugs/321/#3451
   2016-09-18

 * sysinfo.PbdMPT7yUD
   x73rmin8r [https://www.reddit.com/user/x73rmin8r]
   https://github.com/linuxwacom/wacom-hid-descriptors/issues/5
   2017-08-28
